cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles (145 km) southeast of Cozumel, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northwest across the Yucatan Peninsula, then turning north-northeast across the Gulf of Mexico toward the northern Gulf Coast before accelerating northeast across the Southeast U.S. and exiting near the Mid-Atlantic coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Gulf Coast (likely southeast Louisiana to Mississippi coast)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Storm Surge and Hurricane Watches posted from Intracoastal City, LA, to the Mississippi/Alabama border and further east to the Florida Panhandle
weather_observation.warning_coast: Hurricane and Tropical-Storm Warnings only for parts of the Yucatan Peninsula (no Mid-Atlantic warnings at this time)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Yucatan Peninsula, northern Gulf Coast, inland Southeast, southern Appalachians and Mid-Atlantic coast (including Delaware Bay)
weather_observation.wind: Low chance (≤11%) of brief tropical-storm-force gusts late Thursday night into Friday morning
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along Delaware Bay from Zeta
weather_observation.rainfall: Potential 2–4 inches of rain Thursday night into Friday with isolated higher totals causing localized flooding
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor river or urban flooding possible; brief marine/harbor restrictions likely due to gusty winds and elevated seas
